WEBVTT

00:01.772 --> 00:02.773
HEY.

00:02.773 --> 00:05.106
HEY, HOW WAS THE SKI TRIP?

00:05.106 --> 00:07.138
IT WAS GREAT.
CLAIRE´S FAMILY WAS SO COOL.

00:07.138 --> 00:10.181
THEY LOVED ME.
THEY WERE LAUGHING AT MY JOKES.

00:10.181 --> 00:13.484
YOU DIDN´T TELL ME
THEY WERE DRINKERS.

00:13.484 --> 00:15.216
WHERE´S DAD?

00:15.216 --> 00:17.348
CARMEN, WE DIDN´T WANT TO TELL
YOU THIS BEFORE YOUR TRIP,

00:17.348 --> 00:19.190
BUT THERE WAS A PLANE CRASH,

00:19.190 --> 00:22.193
AND THEY THINK THE LANDING GEAR
MADE BY YOUR DAD´S FACTORY

00:22.193 --> 00:23.554
WAS INVOLVED.

00:23.554 --> 00:25.126
HOW´S HE DOING?

00:25.126 --> 00:27.658
THE LAST FEW DAYS
HAVE BEEN PRETTY TOUGH.

00:27.658 --> 00:29.300
I´M GONNA SAY HI TO HIM.

00:29.300 --> 00:30.331
OKAY.

00:30.331 --> 00:33.134
HEY, DAD...

00:33.134 --> 00:34.565
AAH!

00:38.239 --> 00:41.312
WOW, CARMEN SCREAMED LOUDER
THAN YOUR MOTHER.

00:41.312 --> 00:42.573
YOU GUYS ARE SICK.

00:42.573 --> 00:44.115
I CAN´T BELIEVE YOU MADE UP

00:44.115 --> 00:45.816
THAT HORRIBLE STORY
ABOUT A PLANE CRASH

00:45.816 --> 00:47.278
FOR SOME STUPID PRANK.

00:47.278 --> 00:49.450
ACTUALLY, HONEY,
THAT PART WAS TRUE.

00:49.450 --> 00:51.722
OH.

00:51.722 --> 00:54.585
YOU WERE SUPPOSED
TO WAIT FOR ME.

00:54.585 --> 00:56.127
OH, SORRY, MAX.

00:56.127 --> 00:58.289
YOU CAN HANG YOURSELF
AT SCHOOL.

00:58.289 --> 01:01.332
I BET THAT JANITOR
WITH THE DRINKING PROBLEM

01:01.332 --> 01:02.733
COULD USE A GOOD SCARE.

01:04.195 --> 01:07.338
YOU ARE NOT WEARING THAT
TO SCHOOL.

01:07.338 --> 01:09.270
NOW, GET READY FOR SCHOOL,
BOTH OF YOU.

01:09.270 --> 01:12.103
GEORGE, YOU BETTER HURRY UP,
OR YOU´RE GONNA BE LATE.

01:12.103 --> 01:15.176
I´M JUST TRYING TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT I´M GONNA SAY TO EVERYBODY

01:15.176 --> 01:17.808
THE FIRST DAY BACK
AFTER THE CRASH.

01:17.808 --> 01:20.451
HOW DO YOU GET YOUR MIND OFF
THOSE TWO PEOPLE THAT DIED?

01:20.451 --> 01:22.753
OH, MAN,
IT´S GONNA BE GLOOMY.

01:22.753 --> 01:24.515
WAIT.

01:24.515 --> 01:28.759
YOU CAN´T GO
TO WORK LIKE THAT.

01:28.759 --> 01:30.861
HAVE A GOOD DAY.

01:33.424 --> 01:34.565
[ SPEAKING SPANISH ]

01:34.565 --> 01:36.297
HAVE A GOOD DAY.

01:36.297 --> 01:38.098
[ MUSIC PLAYS ]

01:38.098 --> 01:39.570
MAYBE YOU DIDN´T HEAR ME.

01:39.570 --> 01:42.373
I SAID, "TURN OFF
THE FRICKING MUSIC."

01:42.373 --> 01:43.704
LOOK, I´M TEAM LEADER,

01:43.704 --> 01:47.238
AND I WANT EVERYBODY
ON MY LINE FOCUSED.

01:47.238 --> 01:50.141
ARE YOU SAYING I´M NOT
DOING MY JOB RIGHT?

01:50.141 --> 01:51.642
HUH?

01:51.642 --> 01:53.184
BECAUSE IF YOU ARE,

01:53.184 --> 01:56.147
YOU´RE GONNA BE TAKING A
RIDE ON THE PAIN TRAIN.

01:56.147 --> 01:59.420
BACK OFF, OR YOU´RE GONNA
TAKE A RIDE ON THE...

01:59.420 --> 02:01.392
OUCH BUS!

02:01.392 --> 02:02.653
IS IT ON?

02:02.653 --> 02:04.655
I DON´T KNOW --
DID YOU LEAVE IT ON?

02:04.655 --> 02:06.527
HEY, ERNIE, FRANK,
WHAT´S THIS ABOUT?

02:06.527 --> 02:08.199
HE SAID I´M NOT FOCUSED,

02:08.199 --> 02:10.201
LIKE I´M RESPONSIBLE FOR WHAT
HAPPENED TO THOSE PEOPLE.

02:10.201 --> 02:11.732
I DIDN´T SAY THAT,

02:11.732 --> 02:14.134
BUT MAYBE YOU SHOULD TAKE A
SECOND LOOK AT YOUR STRUT SEALS.

02:14.134 --> 02:16.237
I WOULDN´T BE SURPRISED
IF THEY LEAKED.

02:16.237 --> 02:17.338
IT´S ON!

02:17.338 --> 02:19.340
YEAH, ´CAUSE I LEFT IT ON!

02:19.340 --> 02:20.811
COME ON!

02:20.811 --> 02:22.513
HEY, HEY!

02:22.513 --> 02:26.247
IT´S LIKE TWO MANATEES FIGHTING
OVER ONE HEAD OF LETTUCE.

02:26.247 --> 02:28.219
IF YOU TWO GUYS
DON´T KNOCK IT OFF,

02:28.219 --> 02:30.421
I´M GONNA TAKE A COUPLE
OF THOSE SEALS

02:30.421 --> 02:31.922
AND SHOVE THEM DOWN
YOUR THROATS.

02:31.922 --> 02:34.225
I´D STILL BE ABLE TO BREATHE,
´CAUSE THEY DON´T WORK.

02:34.225 --> 02:36.587
THOSE STRUTS
ARE AIRTIGHT, OKAY?!

02:36.587 --> 02:38.889
AND EVEN IF I DID
PUT OUT A BAD PART,

02:38.889 --> 02:41.462
ONE OF THE INSPECTORS
IS SUPPOSED TO CATCH IT.

02:41.462 --> 02:43.794
WELL, DON´T LOOK AT ME.

02:43.794 --> 02:47.268
I´M NOT THE ONE THEY CALL
"INSPECTOR ALZHEIMER´S."

02:47.268 --> 02:50.170
HEY, HEY,
THIS ISN´T MY FAULT.

02:50.170 --> 02:53.944
I DO MY JOB RIGHT,
AND NOTHING GETS PAST ME!

02:53.944 --> 02:57.808
YOU KNOW, I ONLY PRETEND NOT TO
REMEMBER WHAT YOU SAY,

02:57.808 --> 03:00.251
BECAUSE I LOVE
HEARING YOU BRAG

03:00.251 --> 03:01.852
ABOUT HOW
YOU INVENTED FIRE --

03:01.852 --> 03:04.955
THAT´S RIGHT --
YOU´RE OLDER THAN FIRE!

03:04.955 --> 03:08.419
GIRLS, GIRLS!
YOU´RE BOTH OLD AND NASTY.

03:10.591 --> 03:14.295
THIS IS NOT THE TIME TO START
BLAMING EACH OTHER.

03:14.295 --> 03:16.927
OKAY, WE DIDN´T DO
ANYTHING WRONG,

03:16.927 --> 03:19.500
AND WE´LL
GET THROUGH THIS.

03:19.500 --> 03:22.303
WE´VE BEEN THROUGH TOUGH
TIMES BEFORE.

03:22.303 --> 03:24.435
REMEMBER
THE ASBESTOS SCARE?

03:24.435 --> 03:26.307
[ MURMURING ]

03:26.307 --> 03:30.711
WE WERE NEVER IN DANGER.

03:30.711 --> 03:32.913
NOW, COME ON.
GET BACK TO WORK.

03:32.913 --> 03:34.485
BACK TO WORK.

03:34.485 --> 03:36.447
I NEED TO SEE YOU IN
YOUR OFFICE, BACKSTABBER.

03:36.447 --> 03:38.389
JACK, WHEN ARE YOU GONNA
GET OVER THIS?

03:38.389 --> 03:40.491
I THOUGHT THE COMPANY WAS
SPLITTING UP.

03:40.491 --> 03:42.493
I´M SORRY I PICKED YOUR
BROTHER OVER YOU.

03:42.493 --> 03:44.495
THAT´S ALL WATER UNDER
THE BRIDGE,

03:44.495 --> 03:46.457
YOU 2-FACED, LYING JUDAS.

03:48.359 --> 03:50.431
I WANTED TO GIVE
YOU A HEADS-UP.

03:50.431 --> 03:52.363
NTSB´s INVESTIGATING US.

03:52.363 --> 03:54.405
THEY´RE SENDING A GUY OVER
THIS AFTERNOON

03:54.405 --> 03:56.467
THAT´S GONNA QUESTION
ALL THE WORKERS.

03:56.467 --> 03:58.669
THEY THINK
WE´RE RESPONSIBLE?

03:58.669 --> 04:01.342
DON´T WORRY -- I MEAN, THEY´RE
NOT GONNA FIND ANYTHING.

04:01.342 --> 04:03.614
NOW I´VE GOT TO GO
TO MY OFFICE

04:03.614 --> 04:06.517
AND ERASE A LOT OF STUFF
OFF MY HARD DRIVE.

04:06.517 --> 04:08.449
OH, MAN, JACK --

04:08.449 --> 04:09.850
NO, NO, NO.

04:09.850 --> 04:12.283
GEORGE, IT´S NOT
ABOUT THE CRASH.

04:12.283 --> 04:13.754
IT´S...

04:13.754 --> 04:16.957
I´M WRITING
A ROMANCE NOVEL.

04:16.957 --> 04:20.591
WHY WOULD THE NTSB
CARE ABOUT THAT?

04:20.591 --> 04:23.994
IT´S PRETTY STEAMY.

04:25.996 --> 04:28.639
[ INTRO TO WAR´S "LOW RIDER"
PLAYS ]

04:39.710 --> 04:45.015
♫ ALL MY FRIENDS
KNOW THE LOW RIDER ♫

04:46.417 --> 04:51.392
♫ THE LOW RIDER
IS A LITTLE HIGHER ♫

05:15.386 --> 05:19.019
BENITA LOPEZ --
POWERS BROTHERS AVIATION --

05:19.019 --> 05:22.553
EMPLOYEE NUMBER 594 --
THAT´S IT.

05:22.553 --> 05:24.755
YOU CAN HANG ME UPSIDE DOWN AND
BEAT THE SOLES OF MY FEET,

05:24.755 --> 05:26.957
BUT YOU´RE NOT GETTING
ANY MORE OUT OF ME.

05:26.957 --> 05:28.929
HOW LONG HAVE YOU BEEN
AN INSPECTOR?

05:28.929 --> 05:30.561
ABOUT 30 YEARS.

05:30.561 --> 05:33.103
AND HOW MANY PARTS WOULD YOU SAY
YOU INSPECT IN A DAY?

05:33.103 --> 05:35.566
NOT AS MANY AS YOUR WIFE.

05:37.037 --> 05:40.340
ABOUT 80.

05:40.340 --> 05:42.673
SO, AS AN INSPECTOR,
CAN YOU THINK OF ANY WAY

05:42.673 --> 05:44.875
THAT A BAD PART
MAY HAVE GOTTEN THROUGH?

05:44.875 --> 05:47.618
YOU KNOW WHAT THE PROBLEM
WITH YOU GUYS IS?

05:47.618 --> 05:50.451
YOU GOT TO BLAME SOMEBODY
FOR EVERYTHING.

05:50.451 --> 05:53.023
SOMETIMES, CRAP JUST HAPPENS,
YOU KNOW?

05:53.023 --> 05:55.826
PLANES CRASH,
BUSES FALL OFF CLIFFS,

05:55.826 --> 05:59.029
AND -- AND IT LOOKS LIKE YOUR
MOTHER DID IT WITH A FROG.

05:59.029 --> 06:00.461
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

06:01.992 --> 06:04.765
I THINK WE´RE FINISHED.
THANK YOU.

06:04.765 --> 06:08.469
SEND ME A TAPE.
I THINK I DID A GOOD JOB.

06:13.003 --> 06:14.705
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

06:14.705 --> 06:16.146
HOW´D IT GO?

06:16.146 --> 06:18.609
JUST DON´T SAY HIS NAME
DURING THE CAVITY SEARCH.

06:18.609 --> 06:20.681
IT ONLY ENCOURAGES HIM.

06:25.155 --> 06:27.818
HAVE A SEAT, MR. LOPEZ.

06:27.818 --> 06:29.890
I´VE NOTICED THAT
SOME OF YOUR WORKERS

06:29.890 --> 06:32.663
ARE DEALING WITH
SUBSTANCE-ABUSE PROBLEMS,

06:32.663 --> 06:34.725
BUT THEY´RE
STILL EMPLOYED HERE.

06:34.725 --> 06:38.529
AS THE MANAGER,
HOW DO YOU EXPLAIN THAT?

06:38.529 --> 06:41.502
I GIVE THEM A SECOND CHANCE, BUT
I TAKE THEM OFF THE LINE.

06:41.502 --> 06:43.904
EVERYONE GOING THROUGH REHAB
WORKS IN SHIPPING.

06:43.904 --> 06:47.077
WE EVEN HAVE
OUR OWN DELIVERY SLOGAN --

06:47.077 --> 06:49.540
"WHEN IT ABSOLUTELY,
POSITIVELY

06:49.540 --> 06:51.982
HAS TO BE SOMEWHERE,
SOMETIME."

06:51.982 --> 06:53.814
[ LAUGHING ]

06:53.814 --> 06:57.518
SOMETHING TELLS ME
YOU DON´T LIKE THE FUNNY.

06:57.518 --> 07:00.521
MR. LOPEZ,
THIS IS A SERIOUS MATTER.

07:00.521 --> 07:02.152
I CAN SEE FROM YOUR FILES

07:02.152 --> 07:04.525
THAT YOU´VE HAD
PROBLEMS HERE BEFORE

07:04.525 --> 07:06.657
WITH TENSION CLIPS,
ROLLER BEARINGS, OIL LINES.

07:06.657 --> 07:08.799
BUT THOSE PARTS
WERE REJECTED, OKAY?

07:08.799 --> 07:10.961
ANY PROBLEM WE HAVE, WE FIX.
WE DO A GREAT JOB HERE.

07:10.961 --> 07:13.764
I HOPE SO FOR YOUR SAKE,
BECAUSE IT IS YOUR SIGNATURE

07:13.764 --> 07:15.666
THAT SENDS THESE
PARTS OUT THE DOOR.

07:15.666 --> 07:17.668
OH, I HAVE TO GO TO THE CAR
AND GET ANOTHER TAPE.

07:17.668 --> 07:19.169
YOU MIGHT WANT

07:19.169 --> 07:21.071
TO START TAKING YOUR PERSONAL
BELONGINGS OUT OF YOUR DESK.

07:21.071 --> 07:22.843
WHY WOULD I DO THAT?

07:22.843 --> 07:24.845
BECAUSE WE´RE SHUTTING
THIS PLACE DOWN

07:24.845 --> 07:27.017
UNTIL THE INVESTIGATION
IS OVER.

07:27.017 --> 07:28.178
HOW LONG IS THAT GONNA BE?

07:28.178 --> 07:29.850
IT´S IMPOSSIBLE TO SAY.

07:29.850 --> 07:33.023
IT COULD BE A COUPLE OF WEEKS,
COULD BE FOREVER.

07:33.023 --> 07:35.125
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

07:41.131 --> 07:43.463
GEORGE, I NEED SOME
PERSONAL DAYS NEXT WEEK.

07:43.463 --> 07:45.566
I´M NOT GONNA TELL YOU
WHAT THEY´RE FOR.

07:45.566 --> 07:46.997
I JUST NEED THEM OFF.

07:46.997 --> 07:48.238
TAKE THEM.

07:48.238 --> 07:50.571
IT´S A VERY, VERY
PRIVATE MATTER.

07:50.571 --> 07:52.973
PLEASE, DON´T TELL ME.

07:52.973 --> 07:54.845
IT INVOLVES LASERS.

07:54.845 --> 07:57.077
GINA, IF YOU TELL ME,
YOU´RE FIRED.

07:57.077 --> 07:58.909
WHAT IF I JUST
POINT TO IT?

07:58.909 --> 08:00.911
NO!

08:08.559 --> 08:10.921
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

08:10.921 --> 08:13.994
SAVING MONEY -- I´M MAKING
MY OWN HALLOWEEN COSTUME.

08:13.994 --> 08:17.528
[ Monotone ]
I´M A ZOMBIE.

08:17.528 --> 08:20.200
THIS IS MY KELP MASK.

08:20.200 --> 08:22.633
THIS STUFF IS $40 A JAR.

08:22.633 --> 08:28.008
YOU ARE RIPPING OFF
YOUR CUSTOMERS.

08:28.008 --> 08:29.880
MAX, WITH EVERYTHING
THAT´S GOING ON,

08:29.880 --> 08:33.714
THIS IS NOT THE BEST HALLOWEEN
TO BE GOING AS SOMEBODY DEAD.

08:33.714 --> 08:36.547
AND AS FOR THAT MASK,
YOUNG MAN,

08:36.547 --> 08:38.949
LEAVE IT ON FOR
ANOTHER 20 MINUTES.

08:38.949 --> 08:40.290
IT´LL CLEAN YOUR PORES.

08:42.122 --> 08:44.094
WHY ARE YOU HOME SO EARLY?

08:44.094 --> 08:47.628
THE NTSB SHUT DOWN THE FACTORY
TO INVESTIGATE THE CRASH.

08:47.628 --> 08:49.129
WHAT? THAT´S NOT FAIR.

08:49.129 --> 08:51.161
THEY DON´T KNOW
WHAT WENT WRONG,

08:51.161 --> 08:53.203
BUT THEY´RE PUTTING
YOU OUT OF WORK,

08:53.203 --> 08:55.065
TAKING MONEY
OUT OF OUR POCKETS?

08:55.065 --> 08:57.237
IT´S GONNA BE OKAY, BABY.
IT´S ALMOST HALLOWEEN.

08:57.237 --> 08:59.810
AND WHEN THE NEIGHBORHOOD
KIDS EGG THE HOUSE,

08:59.810 --> 09:01.912
I´M GONNA RUN OUT THERE WITH
SOME CHORIZO,

09:01.912 --> 09:04.615
AND WE´LL MAKE AN OMELET
ON THE PORCH.

09:04.615 --> 09:05.876
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

09:05.876 --> 09:08.318
IF IT´S A GIRL SCOUT,
KNOCK HER DOWN.

09:08.318 --> 09:10.621
I´LL TAKE HER COOKIES.

09:10.621 --> 09:14.154
JACK, HI.
COME ON IN.

09:14.154 --> 09:16.556
WHAT NOW, JACK?
THE FACTORY BURN DOWN?

09:16.556 --> 09:18.288
NO, THAT´S PLAN "B."

09:18.288 --> 09:21.892
GEORGE, I´M HERE ´CAUSE
I NEED YOUR HELP.

09:21.892 --> 09:24.665
I´M WORRIED THAT
THE WORKERS ARE GONNA PANIC,

09:24.665 --> 09:26.797
START LOOKING
FOR OTHER JOBS.

09:26.797 --> 09:28.238
WHAT CAN I DO?

09:28.238 --> 09:30.901
YOU´RE FROM THE LINE, GEORGE.
THEY TRUST YOU.

09:30.901 --> 09:33.604
GET THEM TO STICK WITH US,
JUST FOR A FEW WEEKS,

09:33.604 --> 09:34.805
JUST TILL WE´RE CLEARED.

09:34.805 --> 09:37.648
WE CAN´T AFFORD
TO LOSE ANYBODY

09:37.648 --> 09:41.612
EXCEPT, MAYBE, YOUR MOM.

09:41.612 --> 09:43.313
SHE´S A GOOD WORKER,

09:43.313 --> 09:45.716
BUT, GEORGE, SHE GETS DRUNK,

09:45.716 --> 09:48.989
AND SHE CRANK-CALLS MY HOUSE
LATE AT NIGHT.

09:48.989 --> 09:52.663
GEORGE, JUST DON´T LET
ANYBODY QUIT, HUH?

09:52.663 --> 09:54.324
I´M COUNTING ON YOU.

09:54.324 --> 09:56.126
HEY, MOM, IT´S WORKING.

09:56.126 --> 09:59.630
I CAN FEEL MY PORES
BEING CLEANED.

09:59.630 --> 10:02.132
DON´T JUST DO THIS FOR ME.

10:02.132 --> 10:05.305
DO IT FOR
YOUR LITTLE GIRL.

10:20.320 --> 10:21.922
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS DOING?

10:21.922 --> 10:24.855
THOSE FOOLS
ARE LOOKING FOR WORK.

10:24.855 --> 10:26.326
YOU, TOO, ERNIE?

10:26.326 --> 10:28.829
NO, I´M LOOKING AT
LAST NIGHT´S LOTTO NUMBERS.

10:28.829 --> 10:30.360
OH.

10:30.360 --> 10:32.703
NOW I´M LOOKING FOR WORK.

10:32.703 --> 10:34.304
PUT THAT AWAY.

10:34.304 --> 10:36.707
LISTEN UP --
I WANT TO SAY SOMETHING.

10:36.707 --> 10:38.969
[ CELLULAR PHONE RINGS ]

10:38.969 --> 10:40.841
YOU GONNA GET THAT, FRANK?

10:40.841 --> 10:43.213
UH, MY OLD LADY
DOESN´T KNOW I´M OUT OF WORK,

10:43.213 --> 10:45.976
AND I DON´T WANT HER TO KNOW
I´M AT A BAR.

10:45.976 --> 10:48.348
GO AHEAD AND GET IT.
I´LL HELP YOU OUT.

10:48.348 --> 10:49.820
ALL RIGHT.

10:49.820 --> 10:51.181
HEY, SWEETHEART.

10:51.181 --> 10:53.383
FRANK, THAT BETTER
NOT BE A PERSONAL CALL!

10:53.383 --> 10:54.955
ARE YOU CRAZY?!

10:54.955 --> 10:58.258
I GOT TO GO. THE FATHEAD´S
ALL OVER MY JUNK AGAIN.

10:58.258 --> 11:00.160
THANKS, GEORGE.

11:00.160 --> 11:02.362
LOOK, I CAN´T BELIEVE THIS.

11:02.362 --> 11:05.696
YOU GUYS JUMP SHIP
AT THE FIRST SIGN OF TROUBLE.

11:05.696 --> 11:08.168
WHAT HAPPENED TO LOYALTY?

11:08.168 --> 11:11.101
LOOK, THIS INVESTIGATION THING
IS GONNA BLOW OVER.

11:11.101 --> 11:14.674
WE´LL PULL THROUGH THIS.
WE´RE A FAMILY.

11:14.674 --> 11:17.177
I´M HERE FOR YOU GUYS.

11:17.177 --> 11:20.110
FRANK, YOU HAD YOUR
WEDDING IN MY BACKYARD.

11:20.110 --> 11:22.152
AND, GINA,

11:22.152 --> 11:26.156
I HELPED YOU FIX YOUR ROOF AFTER
THE EARTHQUAKE.

11:26.156 --> 11:28.789
BLAINE...

11:28.789 --> 11:30.761
WHO WAS STANDING
BY YOUR SIDE

11:30.761 --> 11:34.694
WHEN YOU FINALLY DECIDED TO COME
OUT TO YOUR PARENTS?

11:34.694 --> 11:36.897
BLAINE IS GAY?

11:38.829 --> 11:41.001
WELL, NOW I´M
OUT AT WORK, TOO.

11:41.001 --> 11:44.434
WHY DON´T YOU
JUST TELL MY WIFE?

11:44.434 --> 11:48.478
LISTEN, ALL I´M
ASKING FOR IS A COUPLE OF WEEKS.

11:48.478 --> 11:51.812
HEY, GEORGE IS RIGHT.
YOU KNOW, WE OWE HIM THAT.

11:51.812 --> 11:53.814
YOU KNOW, I´M HERE
FOR YOU, BUDDY.

11:53.814 --> 11:55.786
YEAH.
I´M IN.

11:55.786 --> 11:57.147
MAYBE THERE´S SOME WAY

11:57.147 --> 11:59.349
WE COULD RAISE MONEY
AND HAVE AN EMERGENCY FUND

11:59.349 --> 12:01.351
AND GIVE IT TO WHOEVER
NEEDS IT.

12:01.351 --> 12:04.494
TOPLESS CAR WASH.

12:04.494 --> 12:06.326
GOOD IDEA, ERNIE,

12:06.326 --> 12:10.230
BECAUSE THESE ARE THE WOMEN
THAT YOU WANT TO SEE TOPLESS.

12:10.230 --> 12:13.403
HEY, THESE CHICHIS
CAN STILL TURN HEADS.

12:13.403 --> 12:16.867
THEY TURN HEADS,
BUT NOW IT´S MORE LIKE THIS --

12:16.867 --> 12:19.039
UGH, HEY!

12:19.039 --> 12:20.740
HEY, HALLOWEEN´S COMING UP.

12:20.740 --> 12:24.444
AND THOSE BIG HAUNTED HOUSES --
THEY MAKE A FORTUNE.

12:24.444 --> 12:26.416
WE COULD BUILD OUR OWN.

12:26.416 --> 12:28.879
THAT´S A GREAT IDEA, ERNIE.
WE COULD HAVE IT AT MY PLACE.

12:28.879 --> 12:30.851
AND WE COULD CHARGE,
LIKE, 5 BUCKS.

12:30.851 --> 12:32.122
COME ON, LET´S DO IT.

12:32.122 --> 12:33.423
ALL RIGHT, YEAH!

12:33.423 --> 12:35.155
THAT´S A GREAT IDEA!

12:35.155 --> 12:37.988
WE CAN ALL GET DRESSED UP LIKE
SKELETONS AND GOBLINS.

12:37.988 --> 12:39.960
AAH! OH!

12:39.960 --> 12:44.394
HOW DID YOU GET INTO YOUR
COSTUME SO FAST?

12:44.394 --> 12:46.196
GIRLS, GIRLS, GIRLS!

12:48.068 --> 12:50.170
OKAY, WE´RE ALL SET.

12:50.170 --> 12:55.405
NOW HAND THE OLD PROSPECTOR $5
AND COME ON IN.

12:55.405 --> 12:57.878
IT´S OUR HOUSE,
SO I´M GOING FIRST, MOM.

12:57.878 --> 13:00.550
OKAY, HONEY, BUT THIS MAY BE THE
LAST TIME WE TALK,

13:00.550 --> 13:05.415
BECAUSE NO ONE GETS OUT
OF THE HAUNTED MINE ALIVE!

13:05.415 --> 13:08.418
HA HA! AAH!

13:09.459 --> 13:12.893
SO LAME.

13:12.893 --> 13:17.227
Man: GOD, NO!

13:17.227 --> 13:21.331
LADIES FIRST.

13:21.331 --> 13:25.475
I SAID, "NO!"

13:35.515 --> 13:38.148
ARE YOU HUNGRY?

13:38.148 --> 13:42.893
NOT YOU. MY BABIES!

13:42.893 --> 13:44.124
AAH!

13:44.124 --> 13:47.097
[ LAUGHING MANIACALLY ]

13:49.029 --> 13:53.904
YOU WILL NEVER ESCAPE
THE WEB OF CARMANTULA!

13:53.904 --> 13:55.205
AAH!

13:55.205 --> 13:59.039
AAH!

13:59.039 --> 14:01.942
[ GROWLING ]

14:05.075 --> 14:07.477
STAY AWAY, FAIRY GIRL!

14:07.477 --> 14:09.950
THIS GOLD IS MINE!

14:09.950 --> 14:13.323
IF I WERE YOU, I´D GET OUT OF
HERE BEFORE IT WAKES UP.

14:13.323 --> 14:15.625
HUH, HUH?

14:15.625 --> 14:19.229
TOO LATE AND TOO BAD FOR YOU...

14:19.229 --> 14:22.492
BECAUSE I´M FAIRY HUNGRY!

14:23.894 --> 14:26.396
AAH!

14:26.396 --> 14:27.637
SAVE YOURSELF!

14:27.637 --> 14:31.071
THE ONLY WAY OUT
IS THE MINING CAR.

14:31.071 --> 14:33.503
MAN, I HOPE THEY
FIXED THE TRACK.

14:33.503 --> 14:36.907
YOU COULD GET LOST
DOWN THERE FOREVER.

14:36.907 --> 14:39.609
[ Crying ]
I WANT TO GO HOME.

14:39.609 --> 14:42.212
OH, WHY ARE YOU CRYING?

14:42.212 --> 14:43.553
IT´S OKAY.

14:43.553 --> 14:45.885
THIS IS HOW YOU GET OUT
TO SEE YOUR MOMMY...

14:45.885 --> 14:50.060
UNLESS THE GIANT
CAVE SNAKE GETS YOU!

14:50.060 --> 14:52.092
AAH!

14:52.092 --> 14:55.295
NO REFUNDS.
TELL ALL YOUR FRIENDS.

14:55.295 --> 14:57.297
WASN´T THAT FUN?

14:57.297 --> 14:59.629
THE BAT WAS SCARY.

14:59.629 --> 15:01.571
TRY HAVING DINNER WITH IT
EVERY SUNDAY.

15:01.571 --> 15:04.134
COME ON.
LET´S GET SOME CANDY.

15:09.379 --> 15:12.312
AH, NOT TOO MUCH!

15:12.312 --> 15:13.984
AAH!

15:13.984 --> 15:16.987
HAPPY HALLOWEEN!

15:22.322 --> 15:24.995
HEY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING,
YOU OLD BAT?

15:24.995 --> 15:28.928
I´M SUCKING
THE REFRESHING GOLDEN BLOOD

15:28.928 --> 15:31.001
OUT OF THIS CAN.

15:35.465 --> 15:38.708
STAY AWAY!
WHAT ARE YOU?

15:38.708 --> 15:40.310
I´M DEAD.

15:40.310 --> 15:42.973
WELL, STAY AWAY, DEAD KID!

15:42.973 --> 15:45.045
THIS GOLD IS MINE!

15:45.045 --> 15:46.376
IF I WERE YOU,

15:46.376 --> 15:49.949
I´D GET OUT OF HERE
BEFORE IT WAKES UP!

15:49.949 --> 15:55.025
BEFORE IT WAKES UP!

15:56.326 --> 15:59.729
VAMONOS, IT!

15:59.729 --> 16:02.332
MOM...

16:04.334 --> 16:06.096
YOU KNOW WHAT?

16:06.096 --> 16:09.169
JUST GO THROUGH HERE,
AND THERE´S SOME CANDY OUTSIDE.

16:12.372 --> 16:16.046
WHAT´S THE MATTER?

16:16.046 --> 16:18.078
THAT DEAD KID...

16:18.078 --> 16:20.380
WHAT IF I DID THAT?

16:20.380 --> 16:22.482
WHAT -- WHAT
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

16:22.482 --> 16:25.555
WHAT IF I KILLED THOSE
PEOPLE ON THE PLANE?

16:25.555 --> 16:28.218
MOM, WHY WOULD
YOU THINK THAT?

16:28.218 --> 16:30.320
YOU KNOW HOW,
WHEN YOU´RE DRIVING,

16:30.320 --> 16:33.223
AND ALL OF A SUDDEN,
YOU LOOK UP, AND YOU REALIZE

16:33.223 --> 16:36.096
THAT YOU HAVEN´T BEEN
PAYING ANY ATTENTION?

16:36.096 --> 16:38.368
WELL, THAT´S HAPPENED TO ME
ON THE LINE.

16:40.100 --> 16:43.273
I LOOK UP, AND I SEE
A BUNCH OF PARTS I´VE OKAYED,

16:43.273 --> 16:49.679
AND I DON´T EVEN REMEMBER
INSPECTING THEM.

16:52.282 --> 16:53.543
COME ON.

16:53.543 --> 16:55.014
[ Crying ] NO.

16:55.014 --> 16:57.287
COME ON.

16:57.287 --> 17:00.790
OH, MAN, I SHOULD HAVE PUT
A ZIPPER IN THIS THING!

17:07.697 --> 17:10.400
MAX!

17:10.400 --> 17:13.133
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
HERE´S MY CANDY.

17:13.133 --> 17:15.565
OKAY, I DON´T WANT YOU TO KEEP
THIS CANDY IN YOUR ROOM.

17:15.565 --> 17:17.067
I WANT IT IN THE KITCHEN.

17:17.067 --> 17:19.169
HOW MANY PIECES
HAVE YOU HAD THIS MORNING?

17:19.169 --> 17:20.039
NONE.

17:20.039 --> 17:21.511
SHOW ME YOUR TONGUE.

17:23.643 --> 17:25.815
SHOW ME YOUR TONGUE.

17:28.047 --> 17:30.680
MAX, WE HAVE THIS TALK
EVERY HALLOWEEN, OKAY?

17:30.680 --> 17:32.282
NO CANDY BEFORE BREAKFAST.

17:32.282 --> 17:34.624
WAIT A MINUTE.
SHOW ME YOUR TONGUE.

17:34.624 --> 17:36.286
NO.

17:36.286 --> 17:39.489
IT´S NOT
IMPORTANT RIGHT NOW.

17:39.489 --> 17:41.761
YOU WENT INTO MY ROOM LAST
NIGHT TO STEAL MY CANDY.

17:41.761 --> 17:43.293
I KNEW I WASN´T DREAMING.

17:43.293 --> 17:48.138
BEARS DON´T TELL YOU
THEY´RE BEARS!

17:48.138 --> 17:51.401
[ Southern accent ]
I DID NO SUCH THING, PARDNER.

17:55.205 --> 17:57.076
HEY, HOW´S IT GOING, MOM?

17:57.076 --> 17:59.349
PERFECT.
YOU KNOW, NEVER BETTER.

17:59.349 --> 18:02.152
LISTEN, I WAS THINKING,
WHEN THE FACTORY OPENS,

18:02.152 --> 18:04.354
IF YOU DON´T WANT
TO INSPECT ANYMORE,

18:04.354 --> 18:07.086
I CAN PUT YOU BACK
ON ONE OF THE MACHINES.

18:07.086 --> 18:09.519
I GUESS THAT WOULD BE
ALL RIGHT.

18:09.519 --> 18:11.291
I´M GETTING SICK

18:11.291 --> 18:14.124
OF LISTENING TO GINA TALK ABOUT
THAT LASER TREATMENT.

18:14.124 --> 18:16.796
HEY, YOU KNOW WHERE
THEY PUT THOSE LASERS?

18:16.796 --> 18:19.229
NO!
DON´T WANT TO KNOW.

18:19.229 --> 18:21.371
DON´T WANT IT POINTED
TO, EITHER.

18:23.173 --> 18:25.835
BENNY, GEORGE TOLD ME
WHAT HAPPENED LAST NIGHT,

18:25.835 --> 18:28.678
AND I WANT YOU TO KNOW
YOU ARE NOT ALONE.

18:28.678 --> 18:33.143
YOU´RE A STRONG PERSON,
BUT YOU´RE STRONGER WITH US.

18:33.143 --> 18:35.345
WHAT ARE YOU --
PAID BY THE HUG?!

18:35.345 --> 18:36.816
GET OFF OF ME!

18:39.689 --> 18:41.891
SHE SEEMS FINE.

18:43.393 --> 18:46.856
WE CLEARED ALMOST $1,000
LAST NIGHT.

18:46.856 --> 18:50.400
THAT SHOULD REALLY HELP OUT
FRANK AND THE OTHER GUYS.

18:50.400 --> 18:51.901
OH, THAT´S GREAT.

18:53.803 --> 18:56.506
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
WITH THE CLASSIFIEDS?

18:56.506 --> 18:57.737
I´M LOOKING FOR A JOB.

18:57.737 --> 18:59.539
WHAT?

18:59.539 --> 19:03.373
YOU JUST TOLD YOUR MOM
THE FACTORY WAS GONNA REOPEN.

19:03.373 --> 19:05.845
LOOK, I´M JUST TRYING
TO GET HER THROUGH THIS, ANGIE.

19:05.845 --> 19:07.777
ALL RIGHT,
I´M GIVING JACK HIS TWO WEEKS,

19:07.777 --> 19:09.519
BUT MY MOM SHOOK ME UP.

19:09.519 --> 19:12.382
I DIDN´T WANT TO ADMIT THERE WAS
A CHANCE WE MADE A MISTAKE,

19:12.382 --> 19:15.525
BUT SHE´S ON THE LINE, AND IF
SHE THINKS THERE´S A PROBLEM,

19:15.525 --> 19:17.687
THEN WHAT
THE HELL DO I KNOW?

19:17.687 --> 19:19.729
I GOT TO TAKE CARE
OF MY FAMILY.

19:19.729 --> 19:21.691
NOW YOU´RE SHAKING ME UP.

19:21.691 --> 19:23.693
EVERYTHING´S GONNA BE
ALL RIGHT, BABY,

19:23.693 --> 19:25.695
AS LONG
AS YOU BELIEVE IN ME

19:25.695 --> 19:27.697
AND MY ABILITY TO...

19:27.697 --> 19:31.641
PUT PETS TO SLEEP
IN A HUMANE ENVIRONMENT.

19:31.641 --> 19:33.643
I MEAN,
HOW HARD CAN THAT BE?

19:33.643 --> 19:36.746
"HEY, LOPEZ, MR. WHISKERS
IS WAKING UP!"

19:36.746 --> 19:38.848
"I´M ON IT!"

19:40.550 --> 19:42.712
I CAN, UM, DOUBLE
MY HOURS AT LA MARIE,

19:42.712 --> 19:46.256
AND UNTIL THE FACTORY REOPENS,
YOU CAN WATCH THE KIDS.

19:46.256 --> 19:48.588
I´D RATHER KILL
STRANGERS´ PETS.

19:51.521 --> 19:53.793
MOM...

19:53.793 --> 19:56.496
DAD?

19:56.496 --> 19:58.898
[ Voice breaking ]
I LOVE YOU.

20:05.675 --> 20:07.637
ONE LESS MOUTH TO FEED?

20:07.637 --> 20:09.539
YEP.

20:14.914 --> 20:16.586
HEY, GINA, WHAT´S UP?

20:16.586 --> 20:18.888
WELL, I GOT
THAT LASER SURGERY.

20:18.888 --> 20:20.620
I DON´T NEED TO KNOW.

20:20.620 --> 20:23.593
THERE WAS A GIANT MIRROR, AND I
GOT TO WATCH THE WHOLE THING

20:23.593 --> 20:25.825
AS THEY WERE
MAKING IT HAPPEN.

20:25.825 --> 20:27.627
TEQUILA.

20:29.729 --> 20:30.900
JACK-ACK.

20:30.900 --> 20:32.702
WHAT´S UP, BROTHER?

20:32.702 --> 20:35.465
GEORGE, I´M GLAD YOU´RE HERE.
LET ME ASK YOU A QUESTION.

20:35.465 --> 20:37.507
IF YOU WERE A YOUNG
SOUTHERN BELLE,

20:37.507 --> 20:39.609
WHO WOULD YOU BE MORE
ATTRACTED TO --

20:39.609 --> 20:41.911
THE DASHING CAPTAIN
WITH THE PROMISING FUTURE,

20:41.911 --> 20:46.245
OR AN IRISH STABLEBOY
WITH EYES SO BLUE,

20:46.245 --> 20:47.747
YOU COULD SWIM IN THEM?

20:49.719 --> 20:51.881
OH, HELL,
I GOT TEQUILA AT THE HOUSE.
